WEBVTT

00:01.419 --> 00:03.785
You pull into the roll.

00:03.880 --> 00:05.290
It's counterintuitive at first,

00:05.381 --> 00:07.713
but it radically increases your
distance from the enemy.

00:07.800 --> 00:09.336
Aeryn, my module is a
research craft.

00:09.427 --> 00:11.668
It's not built for
hairpin maneuvers.

00:11.762 --> 00:14.674
Would you like to learn
how to do this

00:14.765 --> 00:17.381
or are you content to
continually display
your ineptitude?

00:17.476 --> 00:21.765
My ineptitude?
You mean my improvisation
that kind of bails your sorry military...

00:21.856 --> 00:24.188
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

00:24.275 --> 00:25.640
What is that smell?

00:25.735 --> 00:26.520
What?

00:26.611 --> 00:28.317
It's your hair. It smells.

00:28.404 --> 00:29.985
Zhaan gave me something.

00:30.072 --> 00:31.573
All right.

00:31.657 --> 00:33.693
It smells good.

00:34.452 --> 00:36.363
I like it.

00:37.371 --> 00:39.748
Well, it's not for you to like.

00:40.374 --> 00:41.454
Oh.

00:41.542 --> 00:43.658
Then what's it for?

00:43.753 --> 00:45.869
For me to like.

00:45.963 --> 00:49.171
You don't like that...
I like it?

00:50.635 --> 00:54.503
Personal indulgences can
fracture a small crew.

00:56.474 --> 01:01.810
I would never tell them that
you scented your hair.

01:22.458 --> 01:23.959
No!

01:24.710 --> 01:26.246
Aeryn... Aeryn, no.

01:26.337 --> 01:30.330
No, no, I will not be a slave
to your hormones.

01:30.424 --> 01:33.257
My hormones? Hey, I was lips,
you were tongue.

01:36.389 --> 01:38.721
Why did you do your hair? Huh?

01:38.808 --> 01:40.298
To see if you'd notice.

01:40.393 --> 01:43.260
Standing at attention.

01:43.354 --> 01:46.061
Well, I'll let Zhaan know that
you find her oils pleasing.

01:46.148 --> 01:48.981
It's you | find pleasing.

01:52.238 --> 01:53.728
You want some advice?

01:53.823 --> 01:56.235
Not particularly.

01:56.325 --> 01:59.283
Makes me want to give it
to you even more.

01:59.370 --> 02:03.204
Hey, there's too much pressure.

02:03.291 --> 02:06.124
She's scared of the future.

02:07.086 --> 02:09.327
So why not just live
in the moment?

02:09.422 --> 02:12.334
You come up with that yourself?

02:12.425 --> 02:17.340
Go fast with the body,
slow with the soul.

02:19.098 --> 02:21.339
Maybe you should find
someone like that.

02:21.434 --> 02:23.390
Pilot:
Commander Crichton, Chiana.

02:23.477 --> 02:26.469
Please join the others in
the Command at once.

02:30.568 --> 02:32.308
D'Argo:
Okay, Pilot, they're here.

02:32.403 --> 02:35.145
Now, tell us why have
we stopped moving?

02:35.239 --> 02:38.231
Are you familiar with Automated
Peacekeeper Satellite Weaponry?

02:38.326 --> 02:40.362
Self-Tracking Pulse Cannons?

02:40.453 --> 02:42.318
We are locked in a
cross-targeted helix.

02:42.413 --> 02:45.029
Pilot, give us
immediate Starburst.
-lmpossible.

02:45.124 --> 02:48.582
The initiation of an energy
surge will result in
our destruction.

02:48.669 --> 02:51.160
Is it Scorpius?
Do you think they found us?

02:51.255 --> 02:53.337
There are no vessels
anywhere near.

02:53.424 --> 02:55.255
Then how the frell did
they get here?

02:55.343 --> 02:59.757
Perhaps from the inhabited
star systems on Moya's
sense horizon.

02:59.847 --> 03:03.214
These cannons appear to be
their first line of defense.

03:03.309 --> 03:06.267
Zhaan:
Peacekeeper settlements
this far into the Uncharted Territories?

03:06.354 --> 03:07.264
Goddess help us.

03:07.355 --> 03:08.140
We got to do something.

03:08.230 --> 03:10.266
( praying )
-Something useful.

03:10.358 --> 03:14.852
A representative of the
inhabited system has
been signaling us.

03:14.945 --> 03:18.403
By the yotzl Run, fight,
surrender. Pick one!

03:18.491 --> 03:21.949
Pilot:
Moya chooses surrender.

03:22.036 --> 03:26.245
Resistance by her means death.

03:29.877 --> 03:32.038
My name is John Crichton,
an astronaut.

03:32.129 --> 03:35.292
A radiation wave hit and I got
shot through a wormhole.

03:35.383 --> 03:38.295
Now I'm lost in some distant
part of the universe on a ship,

03:38.386 --> 03:41.753
a living ship, full of strange
alien life-forms.

03:41.847 --> 03:42.597
Help me.

03:42.681 --> 03:44.137
Listen, please.

03:44.225 --> 03:46.056
Is there anybody out there
who can hear me?

03:46.143 --> 03:50.136
I'm being hunted by an insane
military commander.

03:50.231 --> 03:52.597
I'm doing everything I can.

03:52.691 --> 03:55.524
I'm just looking for
a way home.

04:14.296 --> 04:15.456
lam.

04:15.548 --> 04:19.006
Oh, no. No way, Jose.
You keep your mouth shut.

04:19.093 --> 04:21.129
But I am our best negotiator.

04:21.220 --> 04:25.304
Our best self-serving, to hell
with everyone else-iator.
Shut up.

04:25.391 --> 04:29.259
Tyno:
Our scan reveals you,
indeed have no large weaponry or hidden cargo.

04:29.353 --> 04:31.935
Aeryn:
Yes, and despite this ship's
Peacekeeper history,

04:32.022 --> 04:34.513
we are in no way affiliated
with them.

04:34.608 --> 04:38.692
We are as stated, Counselor
Tyno, peaceful.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.646
And as such, we now release you
to travel as you will.

04:41.740 --> 04:43.867
You're not going to shoot?

04:43.951 --> 04:47.034
Well, that was a productive
four arns.

04:47.121 --> 04:48.827
D'Argo:
May we approach your worlds?

04:48.914 --> 04:50.870
We are prepared to pay
for provisions.

04:50.958 --> 04:53.540
I'm afraid that's impossible
during coronation time.

04:53.627 --> 04:55.333
( loud crunch )
(yells in pain)

04:55.421 --> 04:57.662
Rygel:
Coronation time?

04:57.756 --> 05:02.090
I am Dominar Rygel the Sixteenth
of the Hynerian Empire.

05:02.178 --> 05:05.921
Would you turn away royalty
bearing gifts for your
new sovereign?

05:06.015 --> 05:07.971
Escaped prisoners bearing gifts?

05:08.058 --> 05:14.054
Hear me, Counselor Tyno, your
hatred of the Peacekeepers can
never approach ours.

05:14.148 --> 05:17.686
Fate has conspired to forge
this alliance.

05:19.278 --> 05:22.190
The Royal Planet will
receive you.

05:22.281 --> 05:27.571
Understand, as festivities
approach, we are under
strict security.

05:27.661 --> 05:31.700
Weapons of any kind will
result in incarceration.

05:33.209 --> 05:35.245
Was I right?

05:35.336 --> 05:36.667
Yeah, I guess so.

05:36.754 --> 05:38.290
Was I right?

05:38.380 --> 05:40.245
Yes, Rygel, you were right.

05:40.341 --> 05:43.754
Don't ever forget it.

05:48.224 --> 05:49.259
Aeryn, I want to talk.

05:49.350 --> 05:50.931
I want to talk less.

05:51.018 --> 05:53.134
We tried that.
It leads to kissing.

05:53.229 --> 05:54.139
Oh...

05:54.230 --> 05:55.720
That's a joke.

05:55.814 --> 05:57.270
It's to relieve the tension.

05:57.358 --> 06:00.191
Wasn't funny. Just give me
some space, John.

06:01.195 --> 06:03.777
Fine. Have the whole universe.

06:04.990 --> 06:05.820
Chiana!

06:05.908 --> 06:07.273
Chiana:
Yeahl

06:07.368 --> 06:09.359
I'm going down to the planet.
You want to hang?

06:09.453 --> 06:11.865
( breathless ):
Yeahl

06:11.956 --> 06:13.992
That's good.

06:14.083 --> 06:15.698
Cool, can I come in?

06:17.419 --> 06:20.411
( both yelling orgasmically)
Whoa, geez!

06:22.216 --> 06:24.002
Whoa-ho-ho! Bad time.

06:24.093 --> 06:28.553
No, good time.
Sorry, wrong time.

06:28.639 --> 06:32.257
John, my life has been one
crushing disappointment
after the next

06:32.351 --> 06:37.311
but with this girl l have
managed to find moments
of pleasure.

06:42.194 --> 06:44.230
Don't blow it for me.

06:44.321 --> 06:46.528
Never, it's cool.
I'm happy for you.

06:46.615 --> 06:48.025
Good.
-All right?

06:48.117 --> 06:49.778
Good.
-Good.

06:51.370 --> 06:53.201
How come I'm always the
last to know?

07:35.289 --> 07:36.745
(laughing)

07:36.832 --> 07:39.790
So these are the fabled
breakaway colonies.

07:39.877 --> 07:42.414
When they declared independence
and fled from our home systems

07:42.504 --> 07:44.290
no one gave them a chance
of surviving.

07:44.381 --> 07:48.920
And yet, here they are still
hating the Peacekeepers
1,900 cycles later.

07:49.011 --> 07:52.253
And every Peacekeeper attempt
since then to forge a
coalition has failed.

07:52.348 --> 07:55.761
I'd say they enjoy their
freedoms far too much, Aeryn.

07:55.851 --> 07:57.933
Yeah.
-And why not?

07:58.020 --> 07:59.806
Buy you a drink for a few words.

07:59.897 --> 08:01.603
You mean now that
Chiana's occupied?

08:01.690 --> 08:03.305
Have you made a run
at Zhaan yet?

08:03.400 --> 08:04.810
Oh, that is unfair.

08:08.030 --> 08:11.488
Oh, no, no, no, no, I stopped
raving years ago.

08:11.575 --> 08:12.860
It doesn't hurt you.

08:12.951 --> 08:14.691
It's just for the kiss.

08:21.794 --> 08:23.750
It's no taste.
Kind of like an old...

08:30.302 --> 08:32.338
Sorry.

08:32.429 --> 08:36.889
It's great, you know. It's a
whole world designed for
your rutting instincts.

08:36.975 --> 08:39.352
No. No, no, no, no, no.

08:39.436 --> 08:42.303
Try him. He seems to
love kissing.

08:43.607 --> 08:45.268
Oh, no, no.

08:58.205 --> 09:00.571
I am never leaving this world.

09:02.584 --> 09:03.835
Hey.

09:05.796 --> 09:10.506
Jena:
Clavor, my sweet, there's a
Sebacean down here your sister hasn't kissed yet.

09:13.178 --> 09:17.137
You said the borders were
closed. No new visitors.

09:17.224 --> 09:19.886
And you said it wouldn't matter
that my sister could never
assume the throne,

09:19.977 --> 09:21.968
no matter how many suitors
they bring in.

09:22.062 --> 09:25.896
Her chemical compatibility
is irrevocably altered.

09:25.983 --> 09:28.895
You will be king.

09:28.986 --> 09:30.977
Tyno:
Is this Crichton intelligent?

09:31.071 --> 09:33.813
Rygel:
Surprisingly, despite
his appearance.

09:33.907 --> 09:38.241
| find it strange, Counselor
Tyno, that you're in
Coronation Time

09:38.328 --> 09:41.411
and have yet to identify
your crown successor.

09:41.498 --> 09:44.831
As firstborn, it was always
intended for Princess Katralla.

09:44.918 --> 09:48.376
But by law, unless she can find
a compatible mate,

09:48.464 --> 09:51.001
the kingdom will fall to
her younger brother.

09:51.091 --> 09:52.501
She's a slave to our mother.

09:52.593 --> 09:55.255
I'm the only one who'll
recognize the Scarran lmperium,

09:55.345 --> 09:57.802
even if you are the best
they could send.

09:57.890 --> 09:58.879
(growling)

09:58.974 --> 10:01.260
Now, now, you two.

10:03.604 --> 10:07.267
Well, if you're not going
to be king, Clavor,

10:07.357 --> 10:09.348
I'm not going to marry you.

10:12.154 --> 10:14.065
Pilot:
Excuse me, Zhaan.

10:14.156 --> 10:16.898
Why didn't you visit the
Royal Planet with the others?

10:18.494 --> 10:21.076
My solitude is so important
to me, Pilot.

10:21.163 --> 10:25.031
I barely have enough time to
pursue the tenets of my
priesthood as it is.

10:25.125 --> 10:31.041
Being presumptuous, l have
opened all the doors on the
chamber on this tier.

10:31.131 --> 10:36.376
Moya and l are pleased you
have once again chosen
to stay with us.

10:45.813 --> 10:50.352
(sings high-pitched
sustained note)

10:52.444 --> 10:55.311
( note echoing )

10:58.951 --> 11:02.569
Chiana:
Two drops from these little
vials and we can tell if our...

11:02.663 --> 11:04.745
if our DNA is compatible
for children.

11:04.832 --> 11:06.322
D'Argo:
Um, no, no. I...

11:06.416 --> 11:08.202
Come on, what have we
got to lose?
-I don't want to.

11:08.293 --> 11:11.205
Our innocence.
That's what we've got to lose.

11:20.138 --> 11:21.799
Ah...

11:21.890 --> 11:24.267
Hey, hey...

11:24.351 --> 11:26.683
It's just a game for us,
D'Argo, okay?

11:26.770 --> 11:29.056
We don't play by the
rules they do.

11:29.147 --> 11:31.399
The truth is, we're
not compatible.

11:32.943 --> 11:34.729
Well, only our DNA...

11:34.820 --> 11:37.152
(gasping)

11:37.239 --> 11:41.733
not the parts that make
us feel pleasure.

11:41.827 --> 11:43.818
Rygel:
Why is he watching us
so intently?

11:43.912 --> 11:47.325
When's the last time you
saw a Scarran on a
diplomatic mission?

11:47.416 --> 11:50.749
What do you think he wants,
besides killing Peacekeepers,
I mean?

11:50.836 --> 11:54.670
The same thing my former
superiors wanted, a covenant
with this kingdom.

11:57.676 --> 11:58.882
Go away.

11:59.803 --> 12:01.259
Go.

12:09.187 --> 12:10.393
(gasps )

12:10.480 --> 12:12.016
Have you lost your mind?

12:12.107 --> 12:13.392
Do it.

12:13.483 --> 12:14.734
Ewwl

12:20.282 --> 12:21.397
Sweet.

12:21.491 --> 12:23.277
I'm so pleased.

12:23.785 --> 12:25.400
Rygel:
Me, too.

12:26.163 --> 12:27.869
How unexpected.

12:27.956 --> 12:31.289
| wish you both the very
best of fortune.

12:31.376 --> 12:32.491
Thank you.

12:32.586 --> 12:34.076
( laughing nervously)

12:34.171 --> 12:35.331
( both spitting loudly)

12:35.422 --> 12:38.209
(singing sustained note)

12:38.967 --> 12:40.377
Pilot:
Zhaan...

12:41.011 --> 12:42.592
Zhaan!

12:42.679 --> 12:44.294
Pilot, are you calling me?

12:44.389 --> 12:45.299
It's Scorpius.

12:45.390 --> 12:47.722
Scorpius has found us.

12:57.903 --> 13:00.189
Is the Command Carrier
any closer, Pilot?

13:00.280 --> 13:03.272
Still held in abeyance at the
Satellite Cannon perimeter.

13:03.367 --> 13:04.777
Have they spotted our orbit yet?

13:04.868 --> 13:06.108
Confirmed.

13:06.203 --> 13:08.285
Moya senses the
Peacekeeper scan.

13:08.372 --> 13:11.114
Have we got time to retrieve
Crichton and the others?

13:11.208 --> 13:12.368
No.

13:12.459 --> 13:14.199
(sighing)

13:15.253 --> 13:17.790
What if we let them
see us and then...

13:17.881 --> 13:20.042
Starburst.

13:20.133 --> 13:23.546
Scorpius may think we're
all aboard and pursue.

13:24.554 --> 13:26.840
Goddess, please send
us guidance.

13:26.932 --> 13:28.888
Make this the right
thing to do.

13:37.401 --> 13:39.392
Where are D'Argo and Chiana?

13:39.486 --> 13:44.697
Alternately exchanging body
fluids and checking a tracking
station to locate Moya's orbit.

13:44.783 --> 13:46.899
Doesn't that just figure?
Look, let's get that drink
out of your hand.

13:46.994 --> 13:48.985
-Excuse me.
I'm going to sober you up
and get you out of here.

13:49.079 --> 13:50.194
Yeah, in a second, buddy.

13:50.288 --> 13:52.665
Were you once a Peacekeeper?

13:54.418 --> 13:56.875
No.

13:56.962 --> 13:58.498
Oh, it's Counselor Tyno, right?

13:58.588 --> 14:00.499
Look, we got a little problem.
Our ship...

14:00.590 --> 14:04.503
Your friends have been given
access to our Space Command to
find your ship,

14:04.594 --> 14:08.382
but for now if you don't mind.

14:11.852 --> 14:15.515
Look, I'm a little partied out
so if you could maybe...

14:15.605 --> 14:17.311
Please.

14:23.363 --> 14:24.318
Okay.

14:47.262 --> 14:49.378
(lustful sigh)

14:58.440 --> 15:00.305
It's, uh, sweet.

15:00.400 --> 15:02.812
It's sweet. It's kind of
like molasses.

15:03.737 --> 15:04.567
Tyno:
Guards.

15:05.697 --> 15:06.777
Woman 2:
Look at the Princess!

15:06.865 --> 15:08.071
Woman 3:
She's smiling.

15:08.158 --> 15:09.989
Uh-oh.

15:10.077 --> 15:12.318
Cannot be!
-No, Clavor.

15:12.412 --> 15:13.822
Take your claws off me.

15:13.914 --> 15:16.121
My sister is not supposed to be
compatible with another
Sebacean.

15:16.208 --> 15:18.415
And as far as we know,
she isn't.

15:18.502 --> 15:20.493
Do not make a spectacle,
Your Highness.

15:20.587 --> 15:21.622
The kiss was sweet!

15:21.713 --> 15:23.419
They're compatible!

15:24.132 --> 15:25.542
What the hell's going on?

15:25.634 --> 15:27.716
For your protection.

15:27.803 --> 15:30.135
What if their DNA is cohesive?

15:30.222 --> 15:35.637
Then this pawn, whoever he is,
must die tragically within
a solar day.

15:35.727 --> 15:39.265
(growling)

15:46.196 --> 15:50.314
I understand everything you're
almost saying, except am I
under arrest?

15:50.408 --> 15:51.158
Absolutely not.

15:51.243 --> 15:52.449
Good.

15:53.870 --> 15:55.735
Please, try to understand.

15:55.831 --> 15:56.786
I understand.

15:56.873 --> 15:59.330
You asked me to kiss that chick.

15:59.417 --> 16:01.078
You kissed our Princess.

16:01.169 --> 16:03.125
Yeah, and now we're
"compatible"? What the hell
does that mean?

16:03.213 --> 16:06.296
You're the only male we've found
who might be able to provide her

16:06.383 --> 16:07.964
with healthy children.

16:09.344 --> 16:11.426
You want a donation at
the sperm bank?

16:13.140 --> 16:16.007
I want you to consider
marrying her.

16:23.900 --> 16:28.143
You would just have to be
on this side of my life

16:28.238 --> 16:31.446
to understand how frelling
insane that is.

16:31.533 --> 16:35.242
She will be our next Empress.
You would be Regent.

16:35.328 --> 16:37.410
Others would die for
this chance.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.283
See, "die." There's the problem.
There's the "die" part.

16:39.374 --> 16:43.287
All | ask is that you consider
this blessing that's been
laid before you.

16:43.378 --> 16:46.415
"Blessing", Counselor Tyno?

16:46.506 --> 16:50.840
